

=Bio=

"Daniela Del Bene is currently based in Barcelona and works in the EJOLT project and in the redaction of the EJ atlas at the Autonomous University of Barcelona. She has a background in international relations (BA) and anthropology (MA). Her PhD research in Political Ecology and Ecological Economics is on socio-environmental justice and environmental conflicts, especially around water related issues, dams, river management and hydropower. She is member of the association Research & Degrowth, researching on degrowth and diverse epistemologies moving away from capitalism and liberalism, and of social movements working on water related issues in Italy and of the European Water Movement."



